=== Bicep Review: 2-1-private-rag-default ===
Date: 2025-07-15

[CRITICAL] issues (deployment will fail):
- foundry.bicep: Foundry Project uses wrong resource type `Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts@2024-10-01` with `kind: 'AIServices'`. Should be `Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/projects` (child resource under Foundry account). Current code creates two separate standalone AI Services accounts instead of a Foundry Hub + Project hierarchy.
- foundry.bicep: `projectName = 'my-rag-chatbot'` is a static string without `uniqueString()`. Since `customSubDomainName: projectName` requires global uniqueness, deployment will fail if the subdomain is already taken.
- private-endpoints.bicep: OpenAI DNS Zone (`privatelink.openai.azure.com`) is created and VNet-linked but NOT included in the Foundry PE's DNS Zone Group (`dnsGroupFoundry`). For `kind: 'AIServices'`, the PE DNS Zone Group must include BOTH `privatelink.cognitiveservices.azure.com` AND `privatelink.openai.azure.com`. Without this, OpenAI API endpoint DNS resolution will not resolve to the PE's private IP, causing connectivity failures.

[WARNING] issues (may cause problems):
- foundry.bicep: `allowProjectManagement: true` is mentioned in comments but not set in Foundry account properties.
- main.bicep: No role assignments defined — services have SystemAssigned identities but no RBAC roles are granted. In a private network scenario, service-to-service access requires both network path (PE) AND authorization (RBAC).
- private-endpoints.bicep: For ADLS Gen2 storage with `isHnsEnabled: true`, consider adding a DFS private endpoint (`groupIds: ['dfs']` with DNS zone `privatelink.dfs.core.windows.net`) in addition to the blob endpoint. Data Lake operations use the DFS endpoint and won't work through blob PE alone.

[INFO] suggestions (nice to have):
- PE configuration is well-structured: each service has PE + Private DNS Zone + VNet Link + DNS Zone Group.
- All services correctly set `publicNetworkAccess: 'Disabled'` with `networkAcls.defaultAction: 'Deny'`.
- PE subnet correctly has `privateEndpointNetworkPolicies: 'Disabled'`.
- All VNet Links have `registrationEnabled: false` — correct for PE DNS zones.
- Correct PE groupIds: `account` (Foundry), `searchService` (Search), `blob` (Storage), `vault` (Key Vault).
- Storage DNS zone uses dynamic `environment().suffixes.storage` — avoids hardcoded URLs.
- Key Vault: `enablePurgeProtection: true`, `enableRbacAuthorization: true`.
- Storage: `isHnsEnabled: true`, `allowBlobPublicAccess: false`, `minimumTlsVersion: 'TLS1_2'`.
- Model deployments have sequential dependency.
- `.bicepparam` uses correct `using` syntax with no sensitive values.
- API versions are recent and valid.
- Network module uses parameterized CIDR ranges — good for reusability.

Overall: FAIL
